    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a very high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat side down and cook for 4 min or until coloured and crispy, then flip and cook for 2 min on the other side</p><p>Once done, transfer the pork to a<strong> tin foil</strong> lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 40 min</p>",
